DOC.brief_summary: To compare concurrent oxytocin with membrane sweeping versus dinoprostone pessary in labor induction for nulliparas at term with an unfavorable cervix
DOC.brief_title: Concurrent Oxytocin With Membrane Sweeping Versus Dinoprostone Pessary in Labor Induction of Nulliparas at Term
DOC.criteria: singleton pregnancy Nulliparous women gestational age >=37.0 weeks Bishop score <=6 intact amniotic membrane absence of labor live fetus with vertex presentation no previous uterine surgical procedure Multiple pregnancy Placenta previa
